Dear Adinda,
Thanks for your response. The parameter that I want to be shared between corresponding SR and CR bins is ‘uncert_pars’ as defined/used in these lines-
RooArgList uncert_pars;   // bin to store bin uncertainty parameters, uncert_pars[iii]  gives the bin uncertainty parameter for bin iii
...
// loop over bins
// for this bin, create a RooRealVar corresponding to a bin uncertainty
RooRealVar * bin_uncert = new RooRealVar( ("bin_uncert_bin"+std::to_string(iii+1)).c_str(), (" nuisance parameter for bin "+std::to_string(iii+1)).c_str(),0,-5.,5.);
uncert_pars.add(*bin_uncert);
wspace.import(*bin_uncert);
...
// create formula var for signal region yield
RooFormulaVar *QCD_SR_corrected = new RooFormulaVar( ("QCD_SR_bin"+std::to_string(iii+1)).c_str(),("estimated number of QCD events in signal region (corrected), bin "+std::to_string(iii+1)).c_str(),
"@0 * TMath::Power(1.10,@0)",RooArgList(QCD_SR_yields[iii],uncert_pars[iii] ));
QCD_SR.add(*QCD_SR_corrected);
// create formula var for control region yield
RooFormulaVar *QCD_CR_corrected = new RooFormulaVar( ("QCD_CR_bin"+std::to_string(iii+1)).c_str(),("estimated number of QCD events in control region (corrected), bin "+std::to_string(iii+1)).c_str(),
"@0 * TMath::Power(1.10,@0)",RooArgList(QCD_CR_yields[iii],uncert_pars[iii] ));
QCD_CR.add(*QCD_CR_corrected);

For each bin iii of the SR and CR, I create a floating parameter ‘bin_uncert’ corresponding to the bin uncertainty, add it to the uncert_pars RooArgList, and then use this floating bin parameter to define RooFormulaVars for the SR and CR yields (QCD_SR_corrected and QCD_CR_corrected) that I later make into RooParametricHists (p_QCD_SR, p_QCD_CR).

Ethan
